{"id":43154,"date":"2025-03-16T13:17:32","date_gmt":"2025-03-16T09:17:32","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=43154"},"modified":"2025-03-16T13:17:32","modified_gmt":"2025-03-16T09:17:32","slug":"restrict-allah-mercy","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2025\/03\/16\/restrict-allah-mercy\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Rahmah: How astray to restrict Allah\u2019s mercy!"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Jundub reported: A bedouin came, dismounted his camel, and tied it, then he prayed behind the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him. Afterwards, he called out, \u201cO Allah, have mercy upon me and Muhammad and do not share Your mercy with anyone else!\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Do you say he is more lost or his camel? Did you not hear what he said?<\/strong>\u201d They said, \u201cOf course.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>The mercy of Allah before you is vast. Verily, Allah created one hundred portions of mercy and He sent down a single portion, by which the creation is compassionate to one another, its jinn, its people, and its animals. He has ninety-nine portions left. So do you say he is more lost or his camel?<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 18799<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u062c\u064f\u0646\u0652\u062f\u064f\u0628\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u062c\u064e\u0627\u0621\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0639\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0627\u0628\u0650\u064a\u064c\u0651 \u0641\u064e\u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0627\u062e\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0627\u062d\u0650\u0644\u064e\u062a\u064e\u0647\u064f \u062b\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0651 \u0639\u064e\u0642\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0647\u064e\u0627 \u062b\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0651 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u062e\u064e\u0644\u0652\u0641\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u0650